C[How do you play so that a seki results?  A seki is an impass \

between two or more groups.  If one side tries to attack, its \

own group dies.  Often this is two large eyeless groups that \

share two or more liberties, or two large groups with one eye \

each that share one or more liberties.  More complex seki situations \

are possible.

]

(;B[gd]

C[Now if either side plays at A or B, that group will only have \

one liberty and will be captured.  So neither side will play \

A or B, and at the end of the game, both groups are alive 'in \

seki'.

]

